The fact of the matter is this: when you make a reservation for brunch and you still have to wait for your table upon arrival at the restaurant, the reservation is meaningless. I’ve made reservations to similarly busy spots within the city and have been guaranteed to be seated at the appointed time. On the other hand, I’ve been to restaurants who specifically don’t take reservations BECAUSE they’re so busy. Either of these practices I can understand, but waiting at the door of your establishment after making a reservation prior...it’s poor service in my estimation, not to mention poor enforcement of the reservations themselves. Currently standing with a party of five at the front of the eatery (devoid of a server). If this is a regular experience, then the restaurant needs to reevaluate its reservation policy. This review is solely on the wait we experienced upon arrival. Haven’t tried the food yet.

A romantic partner lead me to this humble, charming, and vibrant off-the-cuff pocket of southern culture in Bed-Stuy. A welcoming and warm hostess invited more of my heart into the restaurant’s interior, which I met as spacious, clean and true to its name. My partner had suggested that we meet outside, and I’m thankful he did: a spacious, beautiful backyard space enhanced with an over standing wooden cover dazzled with lights twinkled my time in the summer weather. This lifting outdoor vibe was amplified by a gracious, considerate and responsive server, whose charm and accountability made the cheesy grits even more satisfying. In my vegetarian recommendation, go for those grits, and ponder the potatoes as well. Not only were my dreams made by the Tres Leches French Toast but were my taste buds transported back to town fares of my past, in the most positive aspect of my memory. Be you a Bed-Stuy local, Brooklyn Native or a visitor, absolutely open your eye to the experience of this restaurant.

Oh, Rustik Taven...much improvement needs to happen if you want to keep GOOD business.  Our first ever Brunch with Keith was amazing from start to finish-- considering there was no heat in the middle of January. Keith reassured us that the food would be worth it and his charisma was definitely a plus! Moving forward to our next two visits, even with reservations, the wait time for drinks during dinner and brunch ranged from 30-40 minutes.  For my fiances birthday dinner he was served a RARE, like RARE RARE, steak. After waiting an additional 20 minutes for the waitress only to be told that the CHEF said that that medium rare looks like that. Now look, a MEDIUM RARE steak should not be COLD TO TOUCH. A medium rare should not be PURPLE IN COLOR. We order medium rare every time we have steak.  Rustik Tavern, please figure out a new game plan. You can keep the culture while maintaining the service you are capable of providing. Hiring additional staff should be considered as well.  We look forward to your efforts!

This is Bed Stuy's neighborhood tavern. (Although if you're being gentrification correct, it may belong to Clinton Hill.)  The owner and his staff are like family.  You walk in and see the same friendly faces greet you.  When you're at Rustik you feel as if at home.  The bar is well stocked.  But if you want some fancy mixology experience, this isn't the place for you.  If you're looking to meet people, THIS IS THE PLACE.  The food will surprise you.  It's a few steps above your average bar fare. I recommend the burger (beef or turkey), wings or salmon but I think I've tried the entire menu and it's all good.  They have brunch on the weekends and you cant fo wrong with the chicken and waffles.  When the weather is nice, sit out in the backyard for a quiet dining experience. Ask about their secret event space, perfect for baby showers and birthday parties.  Follow them on social media because there's always something going on from special guest DJs to karaoke and games night.

Definitely enjoyed the decor of the place and if the weather is great, the outside area looked like a great place to sit.
